7. use the UPDATE statement to modify one or more values in each table.

- s table(Supplier):
>> update s set sname='Abhimanyu' where sname='Aryan';
   update s set s_status=20 where sno='S03';
	
- p table(Part):
>> update p set color='Red' where color='Gray';
   update p set p_city='London' where pno='P1';

-sp table(Shipment):
>> update sp set qty=2 where pno='P5';
   update sp set sno='S02' where sno='S01';
   
8. use DELETE statement to remove:

-  1 record from the s(Supplier) table.
>> delete from s where s_status=10;
   
-  1 record from the p(Parts) table.
